race.description: Cbc/Erc Team Of The Century Hcp (C1)
race.comment: Small field after scratchings. SOUTHERN PRINCE (7) resumed with a nose defeat here over 1400m. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. Maps well with a 1.5kg claimer aboard and fitter he's the one they have to beat. OMNIC (1) peaks and will appreciate the extra trip. Has a 1.5kg claim and his numbers are good enough. NAUGHTY SORT (5) is a local who won her Maiden here well enough first-up to be considered. Don't underestimate. DORADUS (2) lightly raced gelding who was third last start over 1500m at Newcastle. Resumes for a new stable and might pay to keep an eye on any market moves with him.
